    h2 Privacy Policy  

    p 
      span Last Updated: 
      span.highlight November 2025

    article.headed-para
      h4 1. Overview
      p Yapper is a simple hobby project and does not aim to collect unnecessary personal information. However, basic data may be stored as part of normal operation (e.g., account info, chat messages).

    article.headed-para
      h4 2. What We Collect
      p Depending on how the app is used, we may store: Basic account information (username, email if provided), Chat messages and metadata, Technical logs needed to keep the app running. None of this is used for advertising, tracking, or analytics.

    article.headed-para
      h4 3. How Your Data Is Used
      p Data is used only to operate the chat app â€” nothing more. We do not sell, share, or monetize your data in any way.

    article.headed-para
      h4 4. No Security Guarantees
      p Although we try to keep things safe, Yapper is not a professional application. We do not guarantee security, encryption, or protection of your data. Please avoid sending sensitive or personal information.

    article.headed-para
      h4 5. Data Deletion
      p Data can be deleted manually by you (where features allow) or automatically by us. Since this is a hobby project, the database may reset or be cleared at any time.

    article.headed-para
      h4 6. Third-Party Services
      p Yapper does not intentionally integrate with third-party trackers or analytics tools. If any third-party library logs data, it is outside our control.

    article.headed-para
      h4 7. Children's Privacy
      p Yapper is not intended for children. Please avoid using the app if you are under 13.

    article.headed-para
      h4 8. Changes to This Policy
      p We may update this privacy policy at any time without notice.

    article.headed-para
      h4 9. Contact
      p Since this is a hobby project, there is no formal support team. If you have concerns, simply stop using the app.

    